events.name: Mr. Choade’s Upstairs Downstairs at The Slipper Room
events.description: Expect adult entertainment at this long-running vaudeville-style shindig, where dance acts are punctuated with comedy performances (or is that the other way around?). Either way, this party is NSFW. Not that this party is anything like W at all. For more info, visit slipperroom.com.

events.name: 90210! The Musical!
events.description: Catch up with ’90s TV characters Dylan McKay, Brenda and Brandon Walsh, Kelly, Steve and Donna in this Off-Broadway musical parody from the people who brought you Bayside! The Musical! and other laugh-out-loud spoofs of popular television and movie personalities. Music is courtesy of Assaf Gleizner and features songs like “Oh Yeah! Dylan McKay!” and “Will Tori Spelling Graduate?”

events.name: Café Carlyle fall 2016 Season
events.description: Cafe Carlyle's fall 2016 season includes the debuts of Laura Benanti and Ana Gasteyer, together with the return of Christine Ebersole, Judy Collins, John Pizzarelli & Jessica Molaskey, and Steve Tyrell. They will be accompanied by Woody Allen's weekly (Monday) engagement with the Eddy Davis New Orleans Jazz Band. The performance schedule is: Laura Benanti (September 27 through October 8), Christine Ebersole (October 11 through October 22), Ana Gasteyer (October 25 through November 5), Judy Collins (with special guest Ari Hest, November 10 through November 19), John Pizzarelli & Jessica Molaskey (November 22 through December 1) and Steve Tyrell (December 2 through December 31). Reservations can be made by phone at 212-744-1600 or via ticketweb.

events.name: Bad Habit
events.description: The gang behind long-running weekly Manhattan girlcentric throwdown Hot Rabbit jumps the river. This larger Bushwick warehouse venue gives alternative queer-party bunnies more space to do what bunnies do.

events.name: Linda Loves Bingo!
events.description: For some reason, drag and bingo just work together, especially when a high-voltage queen like Linda Simpson is running the show. Head to this weekly happy hour game for a wild twist on the classic game show, with dollar store prizes, game-related drink specials, and appearances from burlesque and drag stars.

events.name: Nouveau York at Le Bain
events.description: The good times never stop at The Standard hotel, André Balazs’ west-side party palace, the High Line–straddling edifice whose rooftop lounges have long been inseparable from the City’s nightlife scene. Sundays at Le Bain (one of the aforementioned drinking dens), Nouveau York holds sway from 9pm to 2am. Guest DJs have included Derrick Carter, Dimitri from Paris and Tim Sweeney. For more info, visit their Facebook page.

events.name: Scissor Sundays at the Rusty Knot
events.description: JD Samson (Le Tigre, MEN) hosts this weekly Sunday afternoon tea dance at the Rusty Knot, a charming space that reminds us of our Uncle Ted's basement—the way it was back in 1982. Enjoy drinks, a convivial LGBTQ crowd and some of the best sunset views around. For more info, visit their donyc.com.

events.name: Deep Space at Cielo
events.description: DJ François K. continues to display his love for Jamaican-inspired dub. The weekly celebration of spacey sounds and laid-back dance vibes features frequent guest DJs and a well-heeled crowd of appreciative party people. For more info, visit deepspacenyc.com.

events.name: Battle Hymn
events.description: The Flash Factory, decorated with religious remnants of NYC churches, is the apt venue for this Sunday party for the LGBTQ community in Chelsea. Featuring a house-music-heavy playlist, this all-night fete is hosted by Ladyfag and serves as an homage to the ’80s and ’90s, when club kids and downtown clubs were all the nightlife rage. Plan to stay late and to dance till you can’t.

events.name: Café Carlyle fall 2016 Season

events.name: Monday Night Magic at Players Theatre
events.description: Here's a cure for a case of the Mondays. This long-running evening celebrates the illusory arts with entertainers who specialize in sleight of hand, mentalism, juggling and the like. For more info, visit mondaynightmagic.com.

events.name: Mobile Mondays! NYC 45's at The Bowery Electric
events.description: It's nothing but an old-fashioned good time at this free shindig, where DJs spin 45s of the funk, soul, punk, new wave, pop, salsa, rock, calypso, reggae, R&B and disco varieties (plus, we're sure, a few genres they forgot to mention). For more info, visit mobilemondaysnyc.com.

events.name: ESO!! Mondays at Bembe
events.description: This weekly party in Williamsburg feautres "latin heat and global beats." Going strong for 10 years, this tropical party features fruity drinks and live percussion.

events.name: Dark Water Tuesdays
events.description: Synth-heads, postpunks and ’80s addicts are welcome to grab a drink and move to the sounds of New Order, Severed Heads, the Human League and more at this weekly chill-out session. Drink specials and well-picked horror, sci-fi and anime flicks on the big screen keep you hanging around way later than you’d expect.

events.name: Frankie’s at the Jane Hotel
events.description: DJ Nita Aviance and rotating guests lead fun-seeking ravers, club kids, muscle boys and fashion deviants on a midweek binge in the ballroom. Staying late will be rewarded with live music and drag performances.

events.name: Alton Brown Live: Eat Your Science
events.description: Television food commentator Alton Brown makes his Broadway debut with a live version of his foodie-geek shtick. Expect breathless, data-packed speeches, neat cooking gadgets and audience interaction. The hammy Brown may literally chew the scenery.

events.name: Roots at Cielo
events.description: Dance lovers get their fix every Wednesday night at this Meatpacking club from DJs Louie Vega and Kevin Hedge. The duo offers a selection of Latin- and jazz-influenced beats, and they help anchor the City's house-music scene. For more info, visit cieloclub.com.

events.name: #Misster
events.description: The baddest gals in town (and a sprinkling of dudes) gather on Wednesdays for pop and hip-hop crowd-pleasers, cheap drinks and wild dancing at The Woods in Williamsburg. Past themes include "Missy Elliot Appreciation Night" and "Britney Spears' Birthday."

events.name: Hump
events.description: The kids are all right and keeping hump day alive at this new weekly, Wednesday night LGBTQ party on the Lower East Side. Hosted by promoter Hannah Shoshana Fisher and actor-promoter Paul Iacono, this Rumpus Room shakedown brings out a young, fashionable 20-something crowd and features performances by drag up-and-comer Blake Deadly (get it?). Cover charge is $5.

events.name: Alton Brown Live: Eat Your Science
events.description: Television food commentator Alton Brown makes his Broadway debut with a live version of his foodie-geek shtick. Expect breathless, data-packed speeches, neat cooking gadgets and audience interaction. The hammy Brown may literally chew the scenery.

events.name: Target Free Thursdays
events.description: This weekly program presents free rock, pop, classical, jazz, Latin and swing concerts, along with live music for swing, salsa and tango dancing, inside one of Lincoln Center’s largest public spaces. Performers include musicians from Lincoln Center’s own Juilliard School, Jazz at Lincoln Center and the Chamber Music Society—and many others. For more information, visit lincolncenter.org.

events.name: Bowl Train at Brooklyn Bowl
events.description: When the Roots' Questlove isn't helping out Jimmy Fallon on The Tonight Show, he's hanging out at Williamsburg's signature bowling alley cum rock venue, spinning hip-hop, house, rare grooves—and showing classic Soul Train videos. In a word: awesome. For more info, visit brooklynbowl.com.

events.name: House Party at Webster Hall
events.description: Just Blaze and DJ Soul helm this weekly shindig, bringing all things hip-hop to the East Village. Expect special guests and other well-known promoters to help bring the noise, including Va$htie, DJ Huggy Bear and DJ Sliink. For more info, visit websterhall.com.

events.name: Fridays at Bill's Place
events.description: Tiny Harlem jazz club Bill's Place opened in 2006, but its vibe recalls an earlier time in the neighborhood's famed musical history. (Our inside source describes the venue as "friendly, preservationist, reverent, spirited, welcoming" and, of course, "intimate"—no surprise there, since seats are within touching distance of the musicians.) On Friday and Saturday nights, owner Bill Saxton, who plays sax, leads his Harlem All Stars. For more info and to make reservations, visit billsplaceharlem.com. Also, note: the club is a speakeasy, so it's strictly BYOB.

events.name: Girls & Boys at Webster Hall
events.description: It takes two to tango—or, in the case of this Webster Hall standard, a crowd of 3,000 ladies and gents in the venue’s Grand Ballroom, as it floods with neon luminance and flashing lights. With a techno throwdown featuring some of the biggest names in dance music, this is not your grandfather’s polka party. Get your groove on to a raw and pumping bass, and hear some of the hippest electronic beats drop at the weekly rave. Past DJs have included MSTRKRFT, Justice, Simian Mobile Disco, Vitalic, A-Trak, Bloody Beetroots, Rusko, Neon Indian and more. For more info, visit websterhall.com.

events.name: Hot Rabbit
events.description: This popular weekly party takes place at the new home of Boots & Saddle in the West Village. Come for an LGBTQ-friendly crowd, and be ready to dance. For more information, visit the party's (semi-NSFW) Facebook page.

events.name: The Plume Revue at Duane Park
events.description: Enjoy live jazz, handcrafted cocktails and a bevy of beauties who (literally) shake their tail feathers. Jo Boobs, Harvest Moon, Gal Friday and others keep the entertainment classy, though not safe for work. For more info, visit duaneparknyc.com.

events.name: Shakin' All Over at Home Sweet Home
events.description: DJ Jonathan Toubin and friends man the decks, playing a mix of rare and vintage rock and soul. For more info, visit newyorknighttrain.com.

events.name: Flash Factory Fridays
events.description: Reminiscent of the anything goes New York of the 70’s, this weekly rager features a full gallery of colorful attendees that includes Club Kids, models and famous faces like Zachary Quinto and Alexander Wang. This discotekka offers a new DJ set every Friday with some of the world’s best house and techno DJs taking residence.

events.description: This packed multilevel throwdown, the creation of nightlife queen Ladyfag, features resident spinner Michael Magnan, plus weekly guests.

events.name: The Rub at The Bell House
events.description: This long-running monthly celebrates good times with disco, funk, hip-hop and the like, so gear up for a night of dancing. For more info, visit itstherub.com.

Welcome to Club Baroque, one of New York City’s newest, high end, upscale, luxurious nightclubs located on the buzzing Steinway Street strip in Astoria, Queens. Only 10 minutes from midtown Manhattan and minutes from all major bridges and tunnels. This is an amazing jaw dropping venue that boasts one of the best sound and lighting systems in NYC alongside a spacious 6500 square foot location featuring ornate, yet modern, baroque style décor.
Coupled with delectable menu options and perfectly blended signature cocktails all served by an amazing staff, along with exemplary above and beyond service at each table, we’re intent on providing a memorable night like none other. events.name: Monarch Rooftop Saturdays
events.description:
BookMyBirthday Presents:
MONARCH ROOFTOP FRIDAYS
Join us every Friday at the beautiful and exclusive Monarch Rooftop!
The Scandinavian-chic décor, designed by Natalia Todorova of Gwathmey, Seigal, Kaufman Architects, features an indoor lounge that radiates glamour and allures with seductive appeal, seamlessly connecting to the exterior oasis patio with sliding floor to ceiling glass doors.
Vintage bricks, white painted hand washed wood panels on the walls, teak and grey custom Terrazzo tiles, and raw iron columns evoke a feeling of a Scandinavian summer home with accents of Manhattan elegance. Black pendants designed by Tom Dixon cast gold shadows on the natural tree form bar counter top and glass lighting fixtures project down to reflect on the modern wood walls.
The modern, yet unimposing deep seated upholstered sofas invite guests to relax and bask in the views of Midtown Manhattan, while floor to ceiling silk curtains frame the picturesque view of the iconic Empire State Building.

events.description:
***RSVP FOR FREE ADMISSION AND NO WAIT IN LINE****
PRIVE GROUP Presents:
THE ATTIC ROOFTOP SATURDAYS
Join us each and every Saturday at the beautiful and exclusive Attic Rooftop!
The team that brought The DL and Dinner on Ludlow to the Lower East Side has recently built a rooftop lounge in Hell's Kitchen with sweeping views of Manhattan. The 5,000 square foot bi-level venue, boasting indoor and outdoor space, is located in the penthouse of the Hilton Garden Hotel at 251 West 48th Street near 8th Avenue.  The DL’s Mino Habib and NYC nightlife veteran Paul Seres are at the helm of the space located on the 15th and 16th floors of the property.
Renowned designer Marc Dizon (Hakkasan Las Vegas, Revel, The Darby) was brought in to renovate and redesign the space and took his inspiration from the golden era of Hollywood. The 16th floor rooftop celebrates the bold patterns and relaxed environment of Beverly Hills pool lounges and outdoor gardens while the lower level lounge, with floor to ceiling glass windows, is inspired by the robust architecture of Richard Neutra and the post contemporary Hollywood Hills vernacular.  It's a cozy lounge with a sunken living room feel.  The color palette is silver and grey with warm woods.  Large bars on each level, plush seating, a DJ booth with state of the art sound system and multiple screens integrated  into the design for corporate branding and event branding are some highlights of the space.

events.name: Monsters of MetLife 2 Bears Tailgate Party (Chicago Bears vs. Giants 11/20/16)
events.description:
WELCOMING CHICAGO BEARS FANS TO THE MONSTERS OF METLIFE TAILGATE 2!!! THE BIGGEST BEST BEARS TAILGATE EAST OF CHICAGO!
LAST TIME WE HAD 400+ BEARS FANS TAKE OVER THE BUS PARKING LOT!
  TAILGATE PARTY DETAILS (WE WILL MOST LIKELY BE IN BUS PARKING LOT L4)
We will be setting up in the bus parking area of Giants Stadium Lot L. (We’ll text, tweet, Instagram, and facebook the exact details that morning when the parking lot opens) You should be able to see all the BEARS FLAGS flying high.
We will have a 4-Hour, All You Can Drink and Eat Party Plus We Have A Professional Tailgate Setup Including:   -BEARS FLAGS -KEGS -BEER PONG  -FULL BAR  - CORN HOLE   - FLIP CUP - BEER KEG TAP SYSTEM    - TENTS   - GRILLS -ICE  - etc.  BEARS TAILGATE PARTY (4-HOUR, ALL YOU CAN DRINK BEER, BOOZE, and EAT) - $75   We Continue to Get Bigger and Better Every Year and This Tailgate Will Be Epic! We have bartenders and chefs ensuring you don't have to do anything but enjoy the party! There will be Kegs, Bartenders, Chefs, Beer Pong, Corn Hole, Tents, Sodas, Water, Burgers, Brats, Vegetarian Options etc. Trust me! This is the best tailgate party setup you've ever seen!
TAILGATE PARTY (Kids/Non-Alcoholic) - $50   We welcome young Bears fans and other non-drinkers too.
NEW- PRIVATE BEARS BUS CHARTER - $45 (Limited to first 56 people)
Due to demand we chartered a private luxury bus! I'll pack it with BEERS and It will go directly to the BEARS TAILGATE PARTY and then will take us safely home after the victory! The bus has a BATHROOM and should be much nicer than mass transit.  BUS LEAVES OVERLOOK BAR (44th bet. 2nd and 3rd) around 8am to come directly to the BEARS TAILGATE PARTY.  Tickets limited to the first 56 BEAR FANS! Buy your tickets now!BEAR DOWN!
FAQ's
Do I need to print out my Tailgate Ticket eventbrite purchase?
No.  We have an electronic list, so you should be all good.  It never hurts to have a backup for all those who buy last minute though. 
   
Where is the BEARS TAILGATE PARTY?
We should be in the charter bus parking lot L4, but we won't know exactly until they open the parking lot. We will then post the location on Eventbrite, and Facebook.  You will see all our BEARS Flags on 25' Flag Poles!
 
Where can I join the MONSTER OF METLIFE 2 facebook group to find all the details?
https://www.facebook.com/groups/monstersofmetlife/
 
Is there a BEARS FAN SECTION GAME TICKET?
No, but we are working on it. The Giants don't do group tickets, so everyone has to buy their game tickets somewhere else. 

Does the Tailgate ticket price include entry to the game? 
No.  You have to buy your game ticket somewhere else. 
 
Can I come to the BEARS TAILGATE PARTY even though I already have game tickets somewhere else?
Absolutely! The more BEARS Fans the better! 
 
Can I show up at the Tailgate party and buy a Tailgate Ticket there? 
Yes. Sometimes there is an extra fee, but we always have enough beer and food for walk ups. Please bring cash because sometimes the credit card readers don't work. 
 
My friends are not a BEARS fans can I bring them?
As long as they know that they are at a BEARS Party and aren't jerks, we're open to all fun party people. 
 
Are there refunds if I can't make it to the events?
No. We have to plan food and drink in advance for the people committed and we are buying the tickets from the teams in advance and the don't refund us, so since we can't get refunded we can't offer refunds to you.

events.description:
After much anticipation, Olivia K is ready to share her latest music video for her single "Power," and it's time to celebrate! Come out and be the first to see the video in all its NYC summer glory, and celebrate young artists of color! We'll have live art as well as musical performances, so bring your kids, your wife, and grandparents for fun for all ages!
UPDATE:This party started out celebrating the incredible communal endeavor celebrating Black female power. But, in light of recent events, I think we need to put the power in our hands right this minute! Here's how we're getting involved: 1. Calling the Faithless: write a letter to the electoral voter of your choice, drop 50 cents for a stamp, and we will put it in the mail it same-day!2. We're putting our money where our heart is! Proceeds from the event go to: operational costs of the event, supporting the local community center in Brownsville, and the ACLU!We are excited to see you at this empowering community event.

events.name: Glitter Avenue's Annual Clothing Swap
events.description:
What is a clothing swap?

A clothing swap is a community event to swap gentle used clothing, shoes and accesories among each other, in a posh and organized manner. We have a tailor and a stylist on site to help you restyle your new finds. Trying to reduce our carbon foot print one stitch at a time.
How many clothes can our guest take?
Every clothing swap is different. If we receive more clothing than we expect, we can give away more. If a guest brings 3 pieces, they can take home 3. But if we start the event with a lot of clothing we can let our guest leave with more than what they came in with. 
Why do we organize Clothing Swaps?
The purpose of a clothing swap is to inspire and educate our guests on textile waste. Every year the U.S. generates an average of 25 Billion pounds of textiles per year. That’s about 82lbs per U.S. resident. Only 15% gets donated or recycled.  These clothes go into landfills and decompose releasing methane which is a contributor to global warming

events.name: Liberty at Sunset- Sunday's
events.description:
She's one of the most beautiful women in New York City, and certainly the most popular. Year after year, millions of people from around the globe flock to Manhattan to have a chance to get a glimpse of her, and now you'll have a chance to do so too. Lady Liberty is truly a spectacle, and if you're anything like the rest of country, you'll definitely want to pick the right voyage as you make your way toward her. There's where the Sunset Yacht comes in to play. Every Tuesday through Sunday this magnificent vessel gives you the chance to hope aboard and sail past some of the most memorable landmarks that the Big Apple has to offer. From the Manhattan, Williamsburg and Brooklyn Bridges, to South Street Seaport, Lower Manhattan, and the Freedom Tower, you'll have a chance to take all of these sites in as you cruise by. Last but certainly not least, will be the gorgeous Statue of Liberty, what's considered to be one of the top landmarks in the country. A live DJ will be supplying music to the all-ages crowd on board, so there will be some sounds that accompany the scenery. Presented by OnCruises.com, this voyage that departs from Pier 15 also features a full bar for the adults, so thirsts will be quenched! Get your tickets while you still can because this special event is a hot commodity in the city.
Boarding: 5:00pm Departing: 6:00pm Returning: 8:00pm
* Prices are subject to increase

$4 Beer: Budwesier, Stella Artois, Fat Tire, Pabst Blue Ribbon, Goose IPA and more!$5 Rosé, Sangria & Mimosas!$5 Champagne and Sparkling WineWednesday Special: $20 Bottles of House WineSunday Special:  Half Priced Sangria & Mimosa ALL DAY

FAQs
What forms of payment do you accept?
The Gem Bar only accepts payment in form of Debit/Credit Card (All major Cards accepted - including Amex). Cash tip accepted/preferred. 
Are there ID requirements or an age limit to enter the event?
Drinking patrons must be 21 years or older. No age restrictions on entrance to The Gem
What can/can't I bring to the event?
Outside food is allowed with required purchase at the bar.
Where can I contact the organizer with any questions?
Send all inquires to bwhiteside@thegemhotel.com or contact us on twitter @TheGemHotel 
Do I have to bring my printed ticket to the event?
Ticket is not required.
The name on the registration/ticket doesn't match the attendee. Is that okay?
Ticket is not required.

events.name: FAMILY MEAL a fundraising event series with Bon Appétit
events.description:
Join BA for the launch of our fundraising event series, “Family Meal” where we take over a chef’s restaurant for a one-night-only party that gives diners unprecedented access to an integral back-of-house ritual: family meal. Each night, before customers arrive, a restaurant’s staff shares a meal and discusses the night ahead. Family meal is the food that cooks serve each other—imaginative, simple dishes (maybe lasagna, or tacos, or jerk chicken)—that diners never get to eat. For BA's "Family Meal," we'll completely take over the restaurant to share these off-the-menu dishes. 
All proceeds from ticket sales will go to a charity that supports immigrants’ rights, determined by the hosting restaurant and BA. Immigrants are essential members of the restaurant industry, and they need our support now more than ever. 
 
Monday, November 21st, Wildair, 6pm – 9pm
Chef Jeremiah Stone & Fabian Von Hauske 
Family Meal: Mexican Dinner
Charity: Immigrant Justice Corps

Sunday , December 11th, Olmsted, noon - 2pm
Chef Greg Baxtrom
Family Meal: Brunch
Charity: TBD

Sunday, January 8th, Café Altro Paradiso, Noon- 2pm
Chef Ignacio Mattos
Family Meal: Latin Brunch
Charity: Immigrant Justice Corps

Monday, January 16th, Reynard, 6pm – 9pm

Hundreds of Jewish Singles, each of whom is more desirous of you than the next.


$5 draft beer, 1/2 wine and $8 well drinks (6-7 pm) to ensure the veracity of the first bullet point.

events.name: Thanksgiving Eve After Work Happy Hour & Social Networking Party ~ Free Event
events.description:
This event is being sponsored by Dave Cervini's newyorksocialnetwork.com and several of their partner Meet Up groups. If you have any questions or want to know how many are attending please contact the event host at dave@newyorksocialnetwork.com.


This may be the friendliest and most social After Work Happy Hour you will every experience! Forget about crowded rooftops, long lines to get in and people with attitudes.  New York Social Network founder Dave Cervini personally welcomes members of NYSN and several Social Networking Meet Up Groups to The Lexington Lounge at The Cort Hotel in the heart of midtown this Wednesday to socialize, network and connect in a fun and friendly atmosphere.  The Lexington Lounge is an upscale lounge in the lobby of the Stylish Cort Hotel on 39th and Lex that features a 25 foot bar, a FREE pool table, plus plush ottomans and cozy banquette areas for you to sit back and socialize with all your new friends!
Stop in for a drink or stay a bit longer, you'll be sure to meet other fun and interesting people.  Come alone or bring a friend, either way you will be glad you did. This is a great event for new members to come out and find out what our group is all about plus mix and mingle with long time members and their friends.
The night will feature...
-Drink specials until 8pm
-Fun ice breakers games with prizes
-NYSN staff on hand to welcome you and introduce you to others at the event. 
-Music played at conversational levels
-FREE admission
-A delicious menu is available with discounts till 8pm
Can I come alone? Yes, 95% of those attending come on their own. Our staff will be on hand to welcome you and introduce you to others in the group.
What to expect: 60-100 people ages 20's - 40's
What to wear: Business casual/stylish
How do I get there? Grand Central and Penn Station are just a blocks away.
Why should I come?  To make new friends, meet people from other groups, learn about NYSN programs and events, find out about other things going on with similar groups, network for business, make a personal connection, check out a new place or just get out of the apartment
If you have any questions before you register please e-mail dave@newyorksocialnetwork.com or call 212-873-2256.  We want to make sure that this party is exactly what you are looking for so that you'll come out again and again!

events.name: Transparent Barriers
events.description:
Opening Reception: Friday November 4th, 6pm - 8pm 
November 4th- November 20th
Angelique Brickner is an artist based out of Ashville, NC. She received her BFA from Colorado State University. She exhibits nationally in Juried and curated shows, such as: ‘Figuratively Speaking’ at the Brooklyn waterfront Artists Coalition juried by Lilly Wei, critic for both Art in America and Art News magazines; ‘Visions in Clay’ at the J Horton Gallery in Stockton, California juried by Judith Schwartz writer of Confrontational Ceramics; ‘Beyond the Brickyard’ at the Archie Bray Center for Ceramic Arts in Montana, and ‘A Survey of Ceramic Figurative Art’ at the Baltimore Clayworks juried by artist Adrian Arleo. She has been included in multiple publications including Ceramics Monthly magazine and Five Hundred Figures in Clay by Lark Press. Angelique has also been awarded multiple ‘Best in Show’ awards including Ceramics Annual of America in San Francisco juried by Suzanne Baiserman curator at the Oakland Museum of Art. Brickner was the winner of Van Der Plas Gallery’s 2015 open call, Anthology. Her current. Solo exhibition Transparent Barriers: Phobias seeks to palpate the barriers created in intimate relationships by fear.
Of her work for this exhibition, Brickner says, “ I am interested in the capacity of the human figure in art to relay and express these various psychological states, and it is my goal to have these compositions probe into the various psychological responses of the human experience to the fears that determine so much about our perceptions of what is true. I am fascinated by the impact our fears have on our inability to ‘see’ others and ourselves clearly.”
Much of Brickner’s work can be traced back to her youth in the Texas panhandle, and the isolation she felt growing up there. In this state of isolation, Bricker sought respite in her mother’s coffee table books filled with the works of famous artists. She would copy their works over and over. Through this practice she became deeply inspired by Egon Schiele and Oskar Kokoshka. This education by exclusion has remains extant within her portfolio.

events.name: 12th Annual Armenian Thanksgiving Eve Party/Fundraiser
events.description:
NY/NJ Metro Armenian Organizations to Host 12th Annual Collaborative Thanksgiving Eve Party 
Please join us at Lexicon on Wednesday, November 23rd at 9:30pm.
The event will be hosted by:AGBU YPGNY, NY ASA, AYF-YOARF NJ Arsen & NY Hyortik Chapters, and ARMNET-GNY
Keeping in tune with the giving spirit of Thanksgiving, five Armenian organizations in the New York metropolitan area will be giving back to their patrons a wonderful night of dance and celebration.
The AGBU Young Professionals of Greater New York (AGBU YPGNY), Armenian Network-Greater New York Region, New York Armenian Students’ Association (NY ASA) and Armenian Youth Federation-Youth Organization of the Armenian Revolutionary Federation (AYF-YOARF) New York Hyortik and New Jersey Arsen Chapters cordially invite one and all to a Thanksgiving Eve party on Wednesday, November 23, 2016 at Lexicon. This hot spot, located in a prime midtown location on 54th St, will play host to an amazing array of Armenian and American dance music.
More importantly, the event will continue a tradition of charitable service by the organizers’ sponsorship of four Armenian charities. The organizers will distribute a majority of the event proceeds to benefit the Holy Martyrs Armenian Day School (www.hmads.org) in New York, Hovnanian Armenian School (www.hovnanianschool.org) in New Jersey, AGBU Syria Emergency Relief Fund, and Fund for Syrian Armenian Relief. The young professionals in attendance will certainly enjoy meeting and mingling with friends knowing that, at the same time, they are giving back to these worthy charities.
Don’t miss your chance to celebrate with your fellow Armenian pilgrims, while also helping to support four very worthwhile Armenian causes. Doors to Lexicon open at 9:30pm to partygoers 21 and over (proper ID required). Admission is $30 with a timely RSVP and $40 for those at the door. Please RSVP by no later than Monday, November 21st.

FAQs
Are there ID requirements or an age limit to enter the event?
21+ to enter

Join the Hope Hill community this November 24th for a fun and relaxed day at our 2nd Annual Thanksgiving Day Party - Potluck style. The Hope Hill Community is made up of a diverse group of people - native New Yorkers, out-of-towners, and everyone in between, and we don't think anyone should celebrate this holiday in a restaurant, but rather with a group of people as close to family as you can get. Hope Hill will provide turkey, gravy, and stuffing.

events.name: Sound Healing - Song Leader Mission
events.description:
The purpose of The Song Leader Mission is to combine sound, song, and spirit in group singing to create unity in ourselves, our homes, our communities, and the frontlines of struggle for social justice. 
Join us on 11/11 at 11:11am in Harlem at the seating plaza at 125th Street and 7th Avenue to honor our slain sistas and brothas. We will walk 125th from west to east as we pay tribute to our soldiers whose lives have been taken, whether by agents of the state or other lost souls. In acknowledgement of Veterans Day, we recognize that we are prisoners of war behind enemy lines and we consider any life taken by violence ultimately an act of this systemic oppression. We can't blame the youth, and we won't, but we will get together to heal.
*RAIN DAY 11-25-16 at 2PM*
The Song Leader Mission is a tangible contribution to movement building. The Song Leader Mission aims to address spiritual bankruptcy, increase health and healing, create connectedness, reclaim birthrights to sound healing and singing, re-introduce group singing as an essential frontline tool, and establish the importance of The African world view and legacy to the planet. As Song Leaders, together can help begin to reverse the commodification of music by bringing music back to the people.

events.name: Liberty at Sunset- Friday's
events.description:
She's one of the most beautiful women in New York City, and certainly the most popular. Year after year, millions of people from around the globe flock to Manhattan to have a chance to get a glimpse of her, and now you'll have a chance to do so too. Lady Liberty is truly a spectacle, and if you're anything like the rest of country, you'll definitely want to pick the right voyage as you make your way toward her. There's where the Sunset Yacht comes in to play. Every Tuesday through Sunday this magnificent vessel gives you the chance to hope aboard and sail past some of the most memorable landmarks that the Big Apple has to offer. From the Manhattan, Williamsburg and Brooklyn Bridges, to South Street Seaport, Lower Manhattan, and the Freedom Tower, you'll have a chance to take all of these sites in as you cruise by. Last but certainly not least, will be the gorgeous Statue of Liberty, what's considered to be one of the top landmarks in the country. A live DJ will be supplying music to the all-ages crowd on board, so there will be some sounds that accompany the scenery. Presented by OnCruises.com, this voyage that departs from Pier 15 also features a full bar for the adults, so thirsts will be quenched! Get your tickets while you still can because this special event is a hot commodity in the city.
Boarding: 5:00pm Departing: 6:00pm Returning: 8:00pm
* Prices are subject to increase

 
FAQs
 
What is the refund policy?
There are NO refunds and all sales are final.

Adult Socials Girls night Out!  This is a new monthly event: perfect for ladies curious about the swinger lifestyle or veterans looking to meet & mingle. A great opportunity to meet other ladies in the lifestyle!When: 8pm - 10pmDress: Casual or sexy - your choice! Whatever makes you feel your best! 



Its FREE to attend…however we ask that everyone bring something to share.  The cost of the shared item need not be expensive - about $10.  Suggestions include: 

a bottle of wine


a 6 pack of beer


snacks (fruit / appetizers / cookies / chocolate etc)

Whether you are a single girl or part of a couple, you are welcome to attend, however no men are allowed!  This event is for the girls to get to know each other, without the boys hanging around!
 


Are you a single girl or part of a couple, just getting into the lifestyle?

Or maybe you have questions and hope to ask other girls?You can participate in our "get to know you" games or just relax and mingle at your own pace.  Whether you’re single or dating, get ready to feel more comfortable and confident at a swingers’ event.While held at Bowery Bliss, Manhattan’s premier on-premise swinger club, this is NOT a play party! 

The after-play party starts at 10 PM! While NOT obligated to stay, single females can attend the after party at no additional cost. 
If attending the after party as a couple (have your guys meet you at 10pm), admission is $60 (regular admission is $100 per couple and Club membership is waived).

events.name: Rock the Yacht- Friday Night Party Cruise
events.description:
There always comes a time when you get tired of the same nightlife options that the city has to offer. Sure, NYC is known to have an overabundance of options, but after sticking to the same routine, time and time again, you also get fed up with going to the same places. Well, rather than making your Friday night as mundane as can be, we're giving you the opportunity to shake things up through this special cruise aboard one of the top vessels in Manhattan. Each and every Friday night hop aboard one of the Hornblower Yachts for their "Rock the Yacht" event. There phenomenal fleet features a state of the art sound system, full bar where you can order up your favorite cocktails, and a live DJ that will be putting that sound system to the test as you cruise around Manhattan and take in the best sights and sounds from the outside in. Friday's in the city are meant to be enjoyed, and if you look at your options, they're stunted to only include bars and nightclubs.
Departing from the brand new Pier 15 at South Street Seaport, it's the perfect place to take off from at 9PM. Get your tickets to this special event soon because you won't want to miss any of the action.
Boarding: 8:30pm Departing: 9:00pm Returning: 12:00am
Age Restriction: 21+

events.name: East Village Pub Crawl ★
events.description:
★ All ticket holders agree to the PCNY Terms of Use. Meeting location and detailed instructions confirmed after booking, and via email. ★
Q: Why is the starting location confidential?
A: This is for both quality control and crowd control. NYC bars (especially in neighborhoods like the Village) can easily become over-crowded so meeting details are only provided to confirmed bookings. 
Q: But is it close to my hotel? 
A: Probably. The East & West Village are very famous neighborhoods in Manhattan. No worries: all crawls begin and end within a couple blocks of major subway lines that run 24 hours a day, and also in high traffic areas with plenty of taxi cabs available all hours of the day & night. After all, it is the city that never sleeps! 
Q: What does my $20 get me? 
A: Admission to the #1 weekly party in New York CIty featuring: 4 of NYC's greatest hot-spots, free drinks & drink specials, 100% free admissions, like-minded people, awesome guides, and an unforgettable night out in NYC! 
Q: Is this good for solo travelers? 
A: Hellz yeah! It is very rare to not have solo travelers in attendance. 
Q: What are the bars like? 
A: Events begin in bars with a relatively calm atmosphere for registration & meet-and-greet, and then increase in intensity. 

Q: Is there transportation between the venues? 
A: No. Some guests, however, take it upon themselves to hire a limousine to drive them around a bit before the crawl and then bring them to the first bar. 
Q: How many others will be attending?
A: As many as we can fit, though we do have a limit. 
Q: What time does the last venue close?
A: 4:00 AM (and sometimes later).
Q: What time do we arrive at the last venue?
A: Approximately midnight.
Q: How far do we walk between bars?
A: The venues are very close to each other. About 3-5 minutes.
Q: What if it is raining or snowing? ☂
A: Guests are encouraged to check the weather forecast beforehand, and prepare accordingly.
Q: Can I arrive late to the event?
A: We have a tight schedule to follow. Do arrive on time.
Q: Is there a dress code?
A: Neat fitting, trendy attire is good. No athletic shoes, hoodies, shorts, flip flops, tank tops, or baseball caps. PCNY is not responsible for denied admissions due to inappropriate attire.
Q: What kind of free drinks/specials do we get?

A: We receive exclusive "pub crawl only" drink deals that vary by location such as: complimentary drinks, a free shot with your drink, and buy one get one free drinks!
Q: Is there an age restriction?
A: You must be 21+ to enjoy this night out. Do bring ID, even if you are 100 years old haha. Laws regarding ID's are very strict here.
Q: What is your cancellation policy?
A: Cancellations must be made no later than 48 hours prior to the event in order to be eligible for transfer or refund. Bookings created within 48 hours of an event are non-transferable/non-refundable.

events.name: The Selectors presents: Nothing Gold Can Stay
events.description:
Friday, November 25The Selectors and House of Yes presents:Nothing Gold Can Stay
// Main RoomCraig Richardshttps://soundcloud.com/craig-richards
Nicolás Lutzhttps://soundcloud.com/nicolaslutz
// Front Parlor Taimur Aghahttps://soundcloud.com/taimur-agha
Cry Babyhttps://soundcloud.com/crybaby1
With the much-protested closing of London’s fabric, now more than ever seems a time to refresh our longstanding relationship with Craig Richards. One of the main driving forces behind the club’s musical aesthetic, his Saturday night residency there and its forward-thinking programming propelled the club itself and him alongside it to legendary status. Craig was never one to hog the spotlight at fabric or elsewhere, releasing a slim, highly-regarded discography either as Tyrant with Lee Burridge or later solo, and the abrupt end of the institution calls many things into question for London and for him personally. The Selector’s and House of Yes proudly welcome him back for a rare New York appearance in the demonstration of solidarity and in full faith that he will deliver the highest possible standard of excellence, as he has done everywhere his work was celebrated, just as it was at fabric at BlkMarket Memberships’ The Nothing Special events. Some may remember the sweatbox party last year with Fred P. and Norm Talley we had with Nicolas Lutz; he is one of a rare breed of DJs whose style centers around the art of the chase: seeking the perfect record, mixed perfectly. Like Craig Richards, Dan Bell or Club der Visionaere compatriot Binh, Lutz’s sets are studied affairs stitched seamlessly together that gain rapturous praise from heads while keeping the dancefloor alive in motion, and his unusual ear extends to his label My Own Jupiter. In the next room, House on Mute’s established curator and resident Cry Baby will share the booth with The Selectors’ Taimur Agha for a rare pairing. ‘Nothing Gold Can Stay,’ presented by The Selectors and House of Yes, is a celebration of the impermanence of things and the new discoveries gained by moving forwards. Join us in gold for this costume ball affair.
21+

events.name: Bubble Ball Soccer NYC. Open Pickup Adult Game
events.description:
Bubble soccer NYC is the premier game for local extreme sports / activity lovers! Spend an exhilarating hour facing (and bouncing) off fellow adventure seekers to score goals for your team. It's the most fun you'll have at a soccer game since - ever!
Open Pickup Game
Each session is 1 Hour. Game time will last for 50 minutes. 10 minutes are allocated to explain the rules and organize everyone in teams. This is an open event with a maximum of 20 participants. Up to 10 player will be on the court / filed at any given time.  *Venue is subject to change.
 
Terms and Conditions of Purchase:
 By purchaing this ticket you understand and agree to following terms and conditions.

Elctronic Waivers:
Each participant is responsible for signing the electronic waiver 24hr prior to the game time. 
Each adult participant bring  a valid ID as proof of identification, in order to play. If under the age of 18, the waiver must be signed by a parent or guardian. A copy of the indentification of the parent/guardian must be provided, if the relevant parent/guardian is not in attendence. 
 
 
Paper waiver: 
If the client wishes not to use the electronic waiver facility they must follow the instructions below.
Each adult participant must print and bring their signed waiver, along with a valid ID as proof of identification, in order to play. If under the age of 18, the waiver must be signed by a parent or guardian. A copy of the indentification of the parent/guardian must be provided, if the relevant parent/guardian is not in attendence. 
 
*Participants must arrive 15 minute prior to your event to allow time to process each waiver.  Game start times are strict and there is no flexibilty if the client arrives late. 
 
Parking:
Bubble Ball Soccer NYC is not responsible for providing any car parking facilities. Given the city center locations of the venues, it is the sole responsibilty of the client to allow ample time to secure on street parking.
 
Public Transportation:
Bubbble Ball Soccer NYC does not take responsibility for any delay in public trasportation to the venue. 
 
Game Time:
Each session is 1 Hour. Game time will last for 50 minutes. 10 minutes are allocated to explain the rules and organise everyone into teams. 
8 - 10 Bubble balls will be in play at any time and additional participants will sub in an out during a pause in play.
Up to 25 participants in total.
* All sales are final / no refunds
** In the event of rain or inclememt weather, the game will be recheduled and refunds will not be issued.
*** In the event there are not enough players, the game will be reschuled
 
Promotion and Media.
By purchasing this ticket, you authorize Bubble Ball Soccer NYCt o photograph or film you and to use such photographs of film for printer materials, broacasts, displays, newspaper articles or any digital media and social media.

events.description:
Sophistiratchet Saturdays
Are you a classy, educated professional who likes to wind down after a hard week at work by getting all the way #turnt up to a soundtrack of trap music? If this is the way you like to spend your weekends, then... you just might be sophistiratchet.
so·phis·ti·rat·chet
 (adjective):
A person of highly educated pedigree (academically, socially & otherwise). Fluent in various forms of public etiquette yet is equally knowledgeable of the latest trap music , updated on most prime-time ratchet cable programs & conversant in the tongue of ratchet.
 If you're about that boozy brunch life, then Sophistiratchet Saturdays is the place for you. It's a place where you can let loose without fear of being judged by sidditty, pretentious people. A spot where you can feel free to twerk when Juvenile tells you to back that thing up; a sanctuary where you can freely admit that you are in love with the coco.  
On Sophistiratchet Saturdays, turn up with us as we partake in boozy brunch at Harlem Bar-B-Q from 12:00-5:00pm. Brunch includes appetizers, a delicious entree, and unlimited brunch cocktails (mimosas, bellinis, screwdrivers, hard iced tea, hard lemonade, and frozen flavored margaritas) for 90 minutes, all while NYC's hottest DJs spins the best of R&B, hip hop, and trap music for your listening pleasure. 
There's only one rule: check your bougie attitude at the door (don't worry -- you have our permission to act dignified again when you leave).

events.name: Liberty at Sunset- Saturday's
events.description:
She's one of the most beautiful women in New York City, and certainly the most popular. Year after year, millions of people from around the globe flock to Manhattan to have a chance to get a glimpse of her, and now you'll have a chance to do so too. Lady Liberty is truly a spectacle, and if you're anything like the rest of country, you'll definitely want to pick the right voyage as you make your way toward her. There's where the Sunset Yacht comes in to play. Every Tuesday through Sunday this magnificent vessel gives you the chance to hope aboard and sail past some of the most memorable landmarks that the Big Apple has to offer. From the Manhattan, Williamsburg and Brooklyn Bridges, to South Street Seaport, Lower Manhattan, and the Freedom Tower, you'll have a chance to take all of these sites in as you cruise by. Last but certainly not least, will be the gorgeous Statue of Liberty, what's considered to be one of the top landmarks in the country. A live DJ will be supplying music to the all-ages crowd on board, so there will be some sounds that accompany the scenery. Presented by OnCruises.com, this voyage that departs from Pier 15 also features a full bar for the adults, so thirsts will be quenched! Get your tickets while you still can because this special event is a hot commodity in the city.
Boarding: 5:00pm Departing: 6:00pm Returning: 8:00pm
* Prices are subject to increase

events.name: Little Italy Scavenger Hunt and Cocktails
events.description:
Please read carefully: This event is being sponsored by Dave Cervini's newyorksocialnetwork.comand several of their partner Meet Up groups.  The number of people registered on this Meet Up represent only a portion of those actually attending. If you have any questions or want to know how many are attending please contact the event host at dave@newyorksocialnetwork.com.


Enjoy the sights and smells of one of Manhattan's most iconic neighborhoods with NYSN members and friends for a fun night that includes a lot of socializing, great food, drinks and a little history.
Here is how it works:
-The group will meet for drinks and registration at Forlini's on Baxter Street from 6:30-7pm.
-We will divide everyone into teams of 4-6 (unless you have a team)
-You will have one hour to set out into the heart of Little Italy along Mulberry Street to find as many clues as you can.
-When you are finished the group will return to Forlini's and we will announce the winners!
-After we give out prizes the group can hang out for food and drinks.  We will do a later in the night walk up to a karaoke bar on Mulberry  around 9:30pm.
Can I come alone? Yes 98% of those attending will come on their own.
What are we looking for? You will be looking for bits and pieces of history, fun artifacts and current things that are already a part of the neighborhood. You will be taking some pictures and bringing things back.
Do I need to know anything?  No, the clues are fun, simple and also some are designed to educate.
Dress code: Business casual
What is included?  Just the scavenger hunt.  Food and drinks are extra.

This is one ridiculously cool yacht that comes equipped with the same amenities that you'd get at an upper-echelon nightclub on land - and we all know that New York City has the creme of the crop in that department. Rather than opting for the stereotypical Saturday night in the city, we're giving you the chance to Rock the Yacht...not just this Saturday, but every single Saturday. A state of the art sound system, dance floors, fully stocked bars where you can order your favorite cocktails, and a live DJ spinning the top tracks to keep the vibe at the party alive for hours on end, those are just some of the things that you can look forward to. Just when you think it doesn't get any better, the views come into play. You'll be able to soak in some of the top landmarks in the city while you cruise around Manhattan on this night. events.name: REMEDY with Privacy (US Debut - Lobster Theremin)
events.description:
Privacy (Berlin)R GambleMaroje TAmourette
This upcoming session of Remedy brings a US debut of fresh Berlin talent PRIVACY. Privacy’s style is cemented in Detroit and Dutch electro tradition but draws heavily on distorted EBM sounds, thick bass lines, and industrial leaning melodies. The Australian born, Berlin based producer broke onto the scene a few years back with slammin release on VOID LIMITED. He followed that up with a very well received and now repressed Hypertext EP on LOBSTER THEREMIN. In 2015 he released Human Resource Exploitation Manual EP, again with Lobster Theremin, and the fantastically coherent Command Pattern EP on KLASSE WRECKS which features a remix from Hamburg artist extraordinaire HELENA HAUFF. 2017 will see a release of his on STEFFI and DEXTER’s electro label KLAKSON RECORDS. We can’t wait for that!Aside from producing, Privacy has maintained a busy DJ schedule playing all over Europe and most recently Australia and Japan. He’s often featured on respected European Radio outlets as Intergalactic FM and Berlin Community Radio. We are so PUMPED to host him here in Brooklyn for ya’ll. On support duties will be one of our favorite local DJs, the man behind the label & event series Lost Soul Enterprises, Closed Circuit, Fourth World and countless other endevours, R GAMBLE. He’ll be throwing down a selection of raw, distorted acid, electro and techno. You are in for a treat!Lastly, rounding out the night will be your Remedy residents MAROJE and AMOURTTE with their booty dropping jams.Join us for this REMEDY!

events.name: Body & SOUL's 20th Anniversary
events.description:
Its hard to believe that 20 Years has flown past us so quickly. From our humble beginnings at Club Vinyl to dance music venues across the world, Body & Soul has come a long way. However what hasnt changed in all that time is the reason we do what we do. Our love of music and family has been our driving force. It has never been about color, race, political beliefs or sexual orientation. Its has and will always be about MUSIC!
We are therefore honored and blessed to be able to celebrate 20 years of parties with you all in our home city of New York.
Joaquin "Joe Claussell, Danny Krivit and Francois-K along with Ariel on lights and our dedicated family of staff members bring you our VERY SPECIAL 20th Anniversary party at the amazing Space Ibiza New York on Sunday November 27th.
See You On The Dance Floor!
